<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Refers to the country of origin, in contrast to Argentina and the morphologically similar 
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" family="Cyttariaceae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. argentinensis" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="argentinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">C. argentinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with which 
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" family="Cyttariaceae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="C. novae-zelandiae" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="novae-zelandiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">C. novae-zelandiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously confused.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J.R.Dixon" authorityYear="1975" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Chlorociboria argentinensis" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="argentinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Chlorociboria argentinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having small, allantoid ascospores and lacking tomentum hyphae, but phylogenetically distinct and with smaller ascospores and narrower asci.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
